description:
A Night Of Triumph Live, originally released on VHS back in the day, was remastered in 5.1 sound (DTS and Dolby Digital) for DVD release in 2004, and we figured now was a good time to give it a bit of press. Better late than never, I guess. This DVD captures Triumph appearing live at the Metro Center Arena in Halifax, Nova Scotia on January 16, 1987 in support of The Sport Of Kings release. Looking at this DVD, I was amazed by the clarity - the overall quality of the video. You&amp;#039;ll be hard-pressed to find another 1980s performance by any band with this picture quality. Additionally, the sound is nothing short of spectacular. While the set list is limited to 82 minutes, it does hit upon the band&amp;#039;s best known songs. The three songs (&quot;Tears In The Rain,&quot; &quot;Somebody&amp;#039;s Out There,&quot; and &quot;Take A Stand&quot;) featured from The Sport Of Kings sound great live but certainly show the band&amp;#039;s radio-friendly direction at the time. 

Band:

Rik Emmett - guitar/vocals
Gil Moore - drums/vocals
Mike Levine - bass/keyboards
Rick Santer - additional guitar/keyboards

Tracks:

Tears in the Rain
Somebody&amp;#039;s Out There
Allied Forces
Lay it on the Line
Midsummer&amp;#039;s daydream
Follow Your Heart
Take a Stand
Magic Power
Rock &amp; Roll Machine
Spellbound
Rocky Mountain Way
Fight the Good Fight

